  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Report cards came out today, and I will admit right now that math is not exactly my strongest ability.",
      "zh": "今天發成績單了，我現在就老實承認，數學絕對不是我最強的能力。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My grade there was lower than I hoped, mostly because of one careless error on a problem I actually knew how to solve.",
      "zh": "我那一科的成績比我希望的低，主要是因為一題我明明會的題目上犯了粗心的錯誤。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I felt a small shock seeing the number, then a wave of shame, then finally just a tired kind of acceptance about the whole thing.",
      "zh": "看到那個分數，我先是有點震驚，然後有點羞愧，最後只剩下一種疲憊的接受。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice, glancing at my report card, said with total honesty that hers was even worse, which somehow made me feel a tiny bit better.",
      "zh": "瞄了一眼我成績單的 Bernice，非常誠實地說她的更差，這句話莫名地讓我感覺好一點。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I did not feel able to celebrate my science grade too loudly in front of her, since that seemed a little selfish given how she was feeling.",
      "zh": "考慮到她的心情，我覺得不太適合在她面前大聲慶祝我的自然課成績，感覺會有點自私。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My teacher said the primary reason for most low grades is a simple lack of daily review, not a lack of natural talent.",
      "zh": "我老師說大多數低分的主要原因其實是缺乏每天複習，而不是缺乏天生的能力。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She said it is necessary to repeat difficult topics multiple times before the knowledge truly sticks, especially in math.",
      "zh": "她說困難的主題必須重複多練幾次，知識才能真正記住，數學尤其如此。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I told her I would try a modern study method I found online, and she said any method is fine as long as I stay consistent with it.",
      "zh": "我跟她說我會試試在網路上找到的一種現代化讀書方法，她說只要能持之以恆，用什麼方法都可以。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, hearing about my grade, said with real confidence that seven-year-olds do not have this problem, since nobody grades robot drawings.",
      "zh": "聽到我成績的 William，非常有自信地說七歲小孩沒有這種煩惱，因為沒人會給機器人塗鴉打分數。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At home, Mom did not get mad at all, saying one lower grade will not lead to any real disaster in the long run.",
      "zh": "在家裡，媽媽完全沒有生氣，說一次成績比較低長遠來看不會造成什麼真正的災難。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She said her own report cards were far from perfect too, and she still managed to enter a good university years later.",
      "zh": "她說她自己以前的成績單也遠遠稱不上完美，多年後她還是順利進入了一所不錯的大學。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia simply hugged me and said a report card measures one season of effort, not a whole person's future.",
      "zh": "Sophia 只是抱了抱我，說一張成績單衡量的只是一段時間的努力，不是一個人的整個未來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By dinner, I already felt better, mostly ready to try again next term instead of staying stuck on one difficult number.",
      "zh": "到了晚餐時間，我已經覺得好多了，大致準備好下學期再努力一次，而不是一直卡在一個難看的數字上。"
    }
  ],
